This unexpected ruling has left Russell devastated, while Hamilton has been promoted to the top spot. name: Nic Fink
summary: Nic Fink, a 2024 Team USA swimmer, achieved a historic feat at the Paris Olympics. Balancing a full-time engineering job, Fink overcame obstacles and became the oldest first-time U.S. Olympic swimming medalist since 1904. He earned a silver medal in the men's 100 breaststroke, tying with Adam Peaty, a swimming legend. Fink's success is a testament to his perseverance and the belief that age is not a barrier to achieving dreams. He aspires for gold in Paris and credits his "swim-life balance" for his achievements, inspiring others to strive for greatness regardless of their circumstances.

name: Lee Kiefer
summary: American fencer Lee Kiefer has achieved a remarkable feat by earning her second consecutive Olympic gold medal in women's foil. In a thrilling final, Kiefer emerged victorious over her American teammate Lauren Scruggs, making history as the first American fencer to win consecutive individual gold medals in the event. Kiefer's precision and skill on the fencing piste were evident throughout the competition, as she displayed surgical-like accuracy in her movements. The all-American final showcased the rising stars of American fencing and cemented Kiefer's status as one of the most dominant athletes in the sport.

name: Laurie Hernandez
summary: Olympic Gymnast Laurie Hernandez has revealed her essential beauty and wellness products, including a $10 facial cleanser. She also discussed her role as a UNICEF ambassador, the 2024 Paris Olympics, and her experience with the 2016 Rio Olympics, where she recalls joking with Simone Biles and Aly Raisman. Hernandez spoke about the broadcasting team for NBC's Olympic gymnastics coverage. She admitted losing straight A's in college due to movement class. Her adorable reaction to Team USA's Olympics throwback video has also gained attention. Furthermore, Hernandez commented on Biles' performance during the first day of the 2021 Tokyo Olympics, calling Biles the "silliest goose on the block." NBC Sports provided details on its plans for Olympic coverage in 2024.

name: Manchester United
summary: Manchester United remains committed to their women's team and has begun its U.S. tour with a match against rivals Arsenal. The women's team will temporarily train at St. George's Park. The club has announced a new striker, wearing the number 9 shirt. In a pre-season friendly, Arsenal defeated Manchester United 2-1 in Southern California. A free live stream of the match was available. Manchester United is in talks with West Ham over a potential transfer for defender Aaron Wan-Bissaka. Manager Erik Ten Hag expressed disappointment over injuries to players Leny Yoro and Rasmus Hojlund. A live stream of Manchester United's upcoming friendly against Arsenal in Los Angeles was also available. Finally, ESPN provided an analysis of the Arsenal vs. Manchester United match.

name: South Sudan basketball
summary: South Sudan, the world's youngest country, is making a splash in international basketball. Despite a technical glitch during their Olympic debut, they have shown determination and growth. The team's journey has captured attention, with experts highlighting the transformative power of sports in bringing people together. South Sudan's basketball revolution is not just about winning, but also about inspiring a nation and showcasing the limitless potential of their youth. With a roster that includes NBA veteran Luol Deng and rising star Khaman Maluach, South Sudan is poised to make waves at the Paris 2024 Olympics, proving that even the newest nations can achieve great things on the world stage.

name: Haley Batten
summary: American mountain biker Haley Batten made history at the Paris Olympics, securing the first-ever Olympic silver medal for the United States in this sport. Despite the penalty, Batten's accomplishment is a testament to her exceptional skills and the growing strength of American mountain biking.
